sence at their interior of\nfresh gas capable of sustaining the star formation. In fact the residuals of\nthe tau vs. L_H relation depend significantly on the HI content. HI deficient\ngalaxies have shorter tau than spirals with normal HI content.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 May 2002 10:36:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
